snippet: For debate No. 3, in mid-September, candidates must have donations from 130,000 people and register at least 2 percent in four polls.
lead_paragraph: The national Democratic Party will toughen the requirements for participating in the presidential primary debates this fall, a decision likely to prompt blowback from candidates struggling to gain a foothold in the crowded race.
abstract: For debate No. 3, in mid-September, candidates must have donations from 130,000 people and register at least 2 percent in four polls.

snippet: The justices upheld a law on the disposal of fetal remains in an Indiana law, but declined to hear a case that could have tested Roe v. Wade.
lead_paragraph: Good Wednesday morning. Here are some of the stories making news in Washington and politics today.
abstract: The justices upheld a law on the disposal of fetal remains in an Indiana law, but declined to hear a case that could have tested Roe v. Wade.
headline_main: On Politics: Supreme Court Sidesteps Abortion Question

snippet: Mr. Biden promoted the plan, the first policy of his campaign, at a town-hall event with the American Federation of Teachers in Houston on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Tuesday released the first major policy platform of his campaign, a sweeping education proposal that urges federal investment in low-income schools, supports universal prekindergarten and higher teacher pay, and, he added in a public appearance later, opposes for-profit charter schools.
abstract: Mr. Biden promoted the plan, the first policy of his campaign, at a town-hall event with the American Federation of Teachers in Houston on Tuesday.

snippet: After the president sided with Kim Jong-un’s government in mocking Mr. Biden’s intelligence, Mr. Biden let an aide rebut it instead of taking on Mr. Trump himself.
lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — President Trump sided again on Tuesday with the government of North Korean leader Kim Jong-un in mocking Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s intelligence, an extraordinary alignment of a United States president and an authoritarian regime against an American politician — and an insult that Mr. Biden pooh-poohed by letting an aide rebut it.
abstract: After the president sided with Kim Jong-un’s government in mocking Mr. Biden’s intelligence, Mr. Biden let an aide rebut it instead of taking on Mr. Trump himself.

snippet: Taking a cue from the Voting Rights Act, Ms. Harris’s plan would require some states to obtain Justice Department approval before new laws could take effect.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California unveiled a plan on Tuesday that would require states and localities with a history of unconstitutionally restricting abortion rights to obtain federal approval before such laws can take effect.
abstract: Taking a cue from the Voting Rights Act, Ms. Harris’s plan would require some states to obtain Justice Department approval before new laws could take effect.

headline_print_headline: In Harris Plan, Abortion Laws Would Require U.S. Approval

snippet: Declining to hold big-dollar fund-raisers and rolling out one policy proposal after another, Ms. Warren has strengthened her candidacy, though questions about her financial viability remain.
lead_paragraph: NEWTON, Iowa — To the crowd of Iowans gathered in a school gym on Saturday night, Senator Elizabeth Warren made a request: They should pose a question to the other presidential candidates who come to Iowa seeking their vote.
abstract: Declining to hold big-dollar fund-raisers and rolling out one policy proposal after another, Ms. Warren has strengthened her candidacy, though questions about her financial viability remain.

snippet: On HBO, Instagram — even Fox News — aspirants are having a meta debate: How do you counterprogram a reality-TV president?
lead_paragraph: You can’t miss the peak of Beto O’Rourke’s 2018 Texas Senate campaign in HBO’s “Running with Beto.” Maybe you’ve already seen it, on your phone or in a Facebook post: Mr. O’Rourke responding passionately to a question about N.F.L. players taking a knee to protest racism and police brutality.
abstract: On HBO, Instagram — even Fox News — aspirants are having a meta debate: How do you counterprogram a reality-TV president?

headline_main: In the Democratic Primary, the Media Hits Are the Message

snippet: The competitive lanes are set as candidates vie for black voters, women, younger voters — but they are fluid. One thing seems sure: Joseph R. Biden’s lead will be tested.
lead_paragraph: NEWTON, Iowa — Joseph R. Biden Jr. has built an early lead in the month since he entered the presidential campaign, confidently projecting himself as the Democratic front-runner and the candidate best positioned to defeat President Trump.
abstract: The competitive lanes are set as candidates vie for black voters, women, younger voters — but they are fluid. One thing seems sure: Joseph R. Biden’s lead will be tested.
